    "body" : "<pre><code>int Random = (int)(Math.random()*100);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>if You need to generate more than one value, then just use \nfor loop for that</p>\n\n<pre><code> for (int i = 1; i &lt;= 10 ; i++)\n       {\n        int Random = (int)(Math.random()*100);\n        System.out.println(Random);\n       }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>If You want to specify a more decent range, like from 10 to 100 ( both are in the range ) </p>\n\n<p>so the code would be :</p>\n\n<pre><code>   int Random =10 +  (int)(Math.random()*(91));\n   /* int Random = (min.value ) + (int)(Math.random()* ( Max - Min + 1));\n  *Where min is the smallest value You want to be the smallest number possible to       \n  generate and Max is the biggest possible number to generate*/\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1928123,
      "reputation" : 21,
      "user_id" : 1738120,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1c6512d58da23ca0089407c360d691c0?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "David Behrens",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1738120/david-behrens"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1349959742,
